INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Broccoli", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f260.html: Anecdotal evidence suggests that Broccoli can occasionally induce symptoms of food allergy in sensitised individuals; however, few studies have been reported to date.", "Autumn", "Vegetable", 1)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Carrot", "https://www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f31.html: The fleshy edible taproots of carrots may be allergic to some individuals. Ingestion can trigger oral allergy syndrome or pollen food allergy syndrome with symptoms ranging from swelling of lips, tongue and throat, nausea, dysphonia, itching of the nose and ear to even systemic reactions like anaphylaxis in some.", "Summer", "Vegetable", 2)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Lemon", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f208.html: Citrus seed extracts display antigenic profiles, indicative of close phylogenetic relationships.", "Winter", "Fruit", 3)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Chili Pepper", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f279.html: The genus Capsicum includes C. annuum sometimes known as chili pepper. Allergy to Capsicum species is rare. Symptoms can occur after ingestion or inhalation of spice dust.", "Autumn", "Vegetable", 4)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Parsley", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f86.html: Allergic reactions are rare and limited to individual case reports. Symptoms of urticaria–angioedema, contact dermatitis and anaphylaxis have been described in association.", "Autumn", "Vegetable", 5)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Apple", "https://www.thermofisher.com/allergy/wo/en/allergen-fact-sheets/apple.html: While apple allergy is caused by proteins in the fruit, the level of allergens in an apple is influenced by the apple variety, storage conditions, and degree of maturity. In a 2014 European study assessing fruit sensitization rates, apple ranked as the second most frequent inducer of sensitization (after peach) with a rate of 6.5 percent. While an average apple weighs 200 to 250 grams, as little as 5 grams of apple can generate a reaction.", "Autumn", "Fruit", 6)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Scallion", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f48.html: Sporadic reports of allergic reactions exist, with anaphylactic reactions being especially rare. Onion handling can induce rhinoconjunctivitis, asthma and contact dermatitis.", "Spring", "Vegetable", 7)
INTO Ingredient VALUES ("Milk", "www.thermofisher.com/phadia/wo/en/resources/allergen-encyclopedia/f2.html: The major allergens found in milk are casein in milk coagulum, α-lactalbumin, and β-lactoglobulin in milk whey. Casein possesses a high degree of allergenicity and antigenicity compared to whey proteins and is a heat-stable protein resistant to processing.", "All", "Dairy", 8)

